<subSubSection id="C89655E1E348805DFF70FCAD4550FC6B" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8033066AE348805DFF70FCAD4550FC6B" blockId="3.[178,1085,845,979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646">
Comment: The original description is based on a unique male. The above specimens were collected near the 
<typeStatus id="5F37B8C8E348805DFE28FC8A4632FCC7" box="[490,534,874,895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646">type</typeStatus>
locality. The female tergites IX and X are distinctly asymmetric, a condition observed also in 
<taxonomicName id="478C7DE9E348805DFDACFC6647BEFC23" authority="ASSING 2013" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2013" box="[622,922,901,923]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depravatum">
<emphasis id="B2F8DA78E348805DFDACFC664722FC23" box="[622,774,901,923]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646">L. depravatum</emphasis>
ASSING 2013
</taxonomicName>
from the same mountain range. The previously unknown female secondary sexual characters are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="18B71AEFE348805DFECEFC5D4554FC6B" box="[268,368,957,979]" captionStart="Figs 9-18" captionStartId="6.[178,218,1512,1532]" captionTargetBox="[178,1073,212,1492]" captionTargetId="figure-77@6.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 9-18: Lathrobium barbiventre (9-10), L. rougemonti (11), L. mancum (12-13), and L. bicuspidatum (14-18): (9, 12) female sternite VIII; (10, 11, 13) female tergites IX-X; (14) forebody; (15) male sternite VII; (16) male sternite VIII; (17-18) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 14: 1.0 mm; 9-13, 15-18: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303205" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303205/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1646">Figs 9-10</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
